						<summary>

						<p>On a slab set up in front of the Sitārāmasvāmin temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1576, Jaya, Vaiśākha, śu. 15, corresponding to 1654 A.D., April 21, Friday.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of land for conducting worship and providing offerings to the temple of Sitārāmasvāmi at Muṭṭukūru by a certain Rāmachandra Vīrakavi of the Viśvakarma community.</p>						

						</summary>
